JS numeric literals have three shapes: hex (0x...), decimal (digits[.digits][eExp]), and the spec-defined scientific suffix. Hex is detected by the 0x/0X prefix and consumes hex digits; decimal falls through to digit-or-dot consumption then optional scientific suffix. We accept both lowercase e (101) and uppercase E (69) for the exponent because the spec is case-insensitive there. The whole numeric text is captured as a single TOKEN_NUMBER with the value-conversion deferred to the parser.
