The token dispatcher is mode-sensitive: JSX vs JS context affects what counts as a token start. jsx_depth tracks nested JSX element depth and brace_depth tracks embedded-expression depth; when jsx_depth > 0 and brace_depth = 0 we are inside an element body, so anything other than "<" or "{" starts JSX text. Otherwise we dispatch by lookahead on the first character to the appropriate scanner.
